<h2><I>Kernel::ConstructPerpendicularVector_2</I></h2>


A model for this must provide:
<P>

<TABLE BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=2 CELLPADDING=0 WIDTH=650>
        <TR><TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP WIDTH=25% NOWRAP>
        <I><NOBR>
    <A HREF="Concept_Kernel--Vector_2.html#Cross_link_anchor_473">Kernel::Vector_2</A><A NAME="Function_Kernel::Vector_2_operator696const_Kernel::Vector_2__v+_Orientation_o9;"></A>

        </I></NOBR>
        </TD><TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP WIDTH=75% NOWRAP COLSPAN=2>
        <I><NOBR>
    fo.operator() (  <A HREF="Concept_Kernel--Vector_2.html#Cross_link_anchor_473">Kernel::Vector_2</A> v,  <A HREF="Enum_Orientation.html#Cross_link_anchor_114">Orientation</A> o)
        </I></NOBR>
        </TR><TR><TD WIDTH=25% NOWRAP></TD><TD WIDTH=25% NOWRAP></TD><TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP WIDTH=50%>
    returns <I>v</I> rotated clockwise by 90 degrees, if <MATH><I>o</I></MATH> is
<I><A HREF="Constant_CLOCKWISE.html#Cross_link_anchor_121">CLOCKWISE</A></I>, and rotated counterclockwise otherwise.<BR>

<EM>Precondition: </EM><MATH><I>o</I></MATH> is not <I><A HREF="Constant_COLLINEAR.html#Cross_link_anchor_125">COLLINEAR</A></I>.
        </TD></TR>
